B.TJ=new A.d0("Pre-existing conditions got their own page with an explicit tick-box","All eleven raised it unprompted. A checkbox buried in an assumptions section was never going to fix a misunderstanding this fundamental.","Stanley from Finance summed it up: \"Having it as its own page \u2014 we're not hiding it. It's quite helpful.\" Kerry noted it changes the claims conversation, since customers have declared from the outset.",B.b9)
B.TH=new A.d0("Excess moved to page one","It was missing entirely, which was both a clarity gap and a missed marketing opportunity given it's one of the lowest excesses in the market.","Now visible alongside cover details, presented as a feature rather than a buried disclosure.",B.b9)
B.kb=new A.yQ("Trade-off",2,"tradeoff")
B.Tz=new A.d0("A qualifier was added to the lifetime cover headline","The unconditional wording sets an expectation the policy can't always keep, and pre-existing exclusions are the most common reason a claim is declined.",'Something like "subject to your pet\'s health history" keeps it accurate without changing the meaning for most customers. Flagged to copy and compliance.',B.kb)
B.TE=new A.d0("Interactive components were standardised","The audit found four button styles and three expansion-panel treatments across the flow \u2014 enough inconsistency to make the page feel unconsidered, which doesn't help when you're trying to earn trust.","One token set across buttons, tooltips, modals and toggles. Engineering noted it'd cut maintenance overhead too, with all components being standardised at the time of writing.",B.b9)
B.TG=new A.d0("Mobile was deferred to a follow-up sprint","A full responsive overhaul wasn't realistic in two weeks within MudBlazor's grid, though the designs exist for when development catches up. Mobile is ~35% of traffic but most completions still happen on desktop.","Backlogged, to be picked up once the A/B experiment gives us something to work with.",B.kb)
